OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777334614
OL,3,CHas Keir Starmer proved he didn't lie
OL,4,Cto MPs?
OL,6,FDowning Street officials hope this
OL,7,Fwill persuade Labour MPs that their
OL,8,Fboss has not misled them by saying in
OL,9,Fthe Commons that due process was
OL,10,Ffollowed, and that they will therefore
OL,11,Fvote against the motion sought by Kemi
OL,12,FBadenoch for Starmer to, in effect, be
OL,13,Fput on trial - as Boris Johnson was -
OL,14,Fby the Commons Privileges Committee.
OL,16,FBut the letter is not 100% comfortable
OL,17,Ffor the prime minister.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
